  <span id="freeText16847029619219936016" style="display:none">A great surprise that this book was. Not being one of the most "trendy" by Saramago, this book proved to be much more beautiful and moving than many others written by this great author. <br /><br />The willpower of the Algor family is unbelievably special and Saramago was expert in his narration. Putting problems and solutions in perfect places, in the time when they had to be.<br /><br />Brings to this plot the dog Achado, which, for me, is one of the most important characters, at crucial moments. Showing, through it, the different perspectives that one has about animals, both in the city and in the countryside. <br /><br />Love full of barriers and silences, which should be hugs and kisses, is also present. <br />But anyone who has read Saramago knows that he always finds ways to make hearts and bodies meet. <br />For now, the best book read in 2020.</span>
